result.execSummary:
The defendant Seung Hyuk Chung was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Seung Hyuk Chung is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Seung Hyuk Chung was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:31 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - State will amend count 1 to Disorderly Conduct with a fine and costs and the balance of the counts will be dismissed.  State concurs.  Atty Johnson concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 as amended.  Court orders counts 2,3 & 4 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Johnson.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-$500 fine plus court costs - Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Court orders the cash bond on file be applied to the fine and costs.

Court adjourned at 1:43 p.m.

9:59 a.m.  No appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Erik Johnson present.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Johnson - defendant is continuing treatment and keeping the DA's office updated and requests a plea & sentencing in April.  Court sets for plea & sentencing on April 12, 2016 at 1:30 p.m. 

Court adjourned at 10:00 a.m.

10:24 a.m.  No appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Erik Johnson present.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Johnson - has had numerous discussions with the DA and requests a Status Hearing be scheduled in approx one year.  No objection by DA.  Statement by DA.  Court will set for status hearing on November 23, 2015 at 9:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 10:27 a.m.
for Leave to File Additional Motions

1:30 p.m. Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Johnson confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading and defendant will waive the preliminary hearing today.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.

Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.

State files an information with the court.  Attorney Johnson and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Johnson enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant. 

Court notes bond has been set - $500 cash bond and conditions.  Statement by Atty Johnson and requests a status hearing be scheduled.  Court will set for status hearing on May 11, 2015 at 10:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 1:34 p.m.
(COPY OF) from Atty Erik Johnson to DA Andrew Christenson dated 01/02/2015 - will accept service of the criminal complaint on behalf of the defendant

Defendant is to have No Violent or Abuseive contact with the victim HIC.  Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.

Defendant is to have No Violent or Abusive contact with the victim HIC.  Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.

1:07 p.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court goes over the potential charges.  Court questions defendant regarding address and employment.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court orders a $500.00 cash bond and conditions of:  Defendant is to have No Violent or Abuseive contact with the victim HIC.  Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  DA to notify the defendant of the next court date.

Court adjourned at 1:13 p.m.
